      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOUNT BARKER BOY (3) made a terrific return from a year on the sidelines when he drew on the back row and did some work before scoring by 9 metres at Bendigo. Should only be better for that and is likely to get the favours from this nice draw. Can go through his grades. KEAYANG PASSION (13) has been showing promise, winning his first two starts before chasing MOUNT BARKER BOY as runner-up last time. Draws out on the second line so may need luck at some point but he is capable. CAPTAIN MOLLY (12) is another drawn awkwardly but looks close to a win after placing in both starts off a spell. COLOSIMO (2) deserved the last-start win. Progressive and should not have any excuses from the favourable draw.",
